<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - INSTALLATION - VIBRATION DAMPER
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>VIBRATION DAMPER</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>
                    <emph type="underscr">BE SURE</emph>
                    THE FRONT MOUNTING BRACKET IS MOUNTED TO THE ENGINE
                    <emph type="underscr">BEFORE</emph>
                    INSTALLING THE VIBRATION DAMPER.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the vibration damper as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Attach damper heater
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE4284</emph>
                    to vibration damper or place damper directly onto a hot plate (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600793">7.93</hotlnk>
                        or
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600794">7.94</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ). Mark damper with a thermomelt crayon 198&#176; C (388&#176; F) and heat. When crayon melts,
                    <emph type="bold">using welding gloves</emph>, install damper on crankshaft nose. Be sure that
                    keyway on damper aligns with key on crankshaft.
                    <emph type="underscr">DO NOT</emph>
                    install damper when cold (room temperature) (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600795">7.95</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600793" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5371" filename="../figeg5/EG5371.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.93 Heating Vibration Damper With Damper Heater</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600794" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5372" filename="../figeg5/EG5372.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.94 Heating Vibration Damper On Hot Plate</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600795" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5071" filename="../figeg5/EG5071.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.95 Installing Vibration Damper</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply an RTV bead to to the crankshaft. Install damper retainer and secure with mounting
                    bolts (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_209.xml" xrefid="ef1600796">7.96</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Prevent crankshaft from turning and tighten bolts to the special torque value (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_209.xml" xrefid="ef1600797">7.97</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
